# ansible
Learning ansible

================

# What is ansible?
Ansible is opensource automation and configuration tool and also use to automate tasks.
Ansible provides open-source automation that reduces complexity and runs everywhere. Using Ansible lets you automate virtually any task.


# Steps to install ansible
sudo apt update
sudo apt install software-properties-common
sudo add-apt-repository --yes --update ppa:ansible/ansible
sudo apt install ansible

# Ansible commands

# To ping hosts- 
ansible -i hosts all -m ping

# To run playbook-
ansible-playbook -i hosts file.yml

# to check ansible version
 ansible --version

# list all host in inventory
ansible-inventory -i hosts --list

# Show graph view of inventory
ansible-inventory -i hosts --graph

# test connectivity
ansible all -m ping

# Runs a command on the web servers
ansible web -m command -a "ls"

# Runs shell commands on remote hosts
ansible web -m shell -a "df -h"

# Asks for SSH password instead of using SSH key.
ansible-playbook site.yml --ask-pass

# Asks for sudo/root password
ansible-playbook site.yml --ask-become-pass

# dry run 
--check

# with sudo
-b

